Working with Git properly
https://docs.github.com/en/get-started/quickstart/github-flow
TLDR: you should have
 a main/master branch for what is currently shown on your hosted site
A dev branch used to test new features before they go live
A branch for each feature you work 
Commit messages should follow this: https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/
UI - dont bother making everything yourself use either
https://tailwindcss.com/
https://chakra-ui.com/
Create the repo on Github from the start and add me to every pull request, and I will review them, my Github username is @neeleshj 
Use typescript if you want
